cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper discusses the use of deep learning algorithms for processing brain imaging data to predict progression to Alzheimer's disease. This falls under the intersection of computer science and neuroscience, and specifically the sub-fields of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), neural networks (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and natural language processing (cs.CL) which are all relevant to the analysis of brain imaging data.
